Here, take it!

124
00:11:49,825 --> 00:11:53,337
May the good Lord also guide
your hand and...

125
00:12:06,722 --> 00:12:07,866
Kolyma!

126
00:12:09,346 --> 00:12:11,134
Fingers inward.

127
00:12:11,553 --> 00:12:14,139
Protect your fingers
Protect yours.

128
00:12:14,562 --> 00:12:17,213
Short and swift. Like this!

129
00:12:20,643 --> 00:12:22,585
That way, the wound is bigger

130
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:25,432
and your opponent
dies more quickly.

131
00:12:25,922 --> 00:12:27,745
Palms up,

132
00:12:28,130 --> 00:12:31,294
you turn the blade and slash.

133
00:12:31,330 --> 00:12:35,073
Watch Gagarin,
he's already good

134
00:12:35,779 --> 00:12:38,529
Learned all by himself.

135
00:13:07,429 --> 00:13:11,203
We are here.
This must be less than a kilometer away.

136
00:13:12,069 --> 00:13:14,720
Eyes open
and absolute silence!

137
00:13:29,797 --> 00:13:32,961
It's heroin. He's got 10 kilos.

138
00:13:33,702 --> 00:13:36,735
Grandpa Kuzya, please!
I have three mouths to feed!

139
00:13:37,605 --> 00:13:39,198
Three mouths?

140
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:42,721
- Yes.
- Is that so?

141
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:45,116
Then...

142
00:13:45,701 --> 00:13:49,858
...Let's just start with yours.
- No! Please! No!

143
00:14:44,104 --> 00:14:46,657
There's something you want to ask me?

144
00:14:51,688 --> 00:14:57,090
The answer to the question
you don't want to ask me is quite simple.

145
00:14:57,225 --> 00:15:00,738
There is no place for drugs
in our community.

146
00:15:01,513 --> 00:15:06,532
We Siberians do not dirty
our hands with that stuff.

147
00:15:11,209 --> 00:15:13,097
Come on Mel, hurry up!

148
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:15,490
I'm trying!
Not so easy, you know.

149
00:15:27,339 --> 00:15:30,534
- Move over!
- Get out of there!

150
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:33,505
Get out of there, you idiot!

151
00:15:37,291 --> 00:15:39,811
Three fucking Georgians!

152
00:15:41,674 --> 00:15:45,220
They stole my stamps,
the ones that I had just bought!

153
00:15:45,290 --> 00:15:47,843
And so you started bawling
right in front of them?

154
00:15:47,915 --> 00:15:50,729
Even the painting with Stalin!

155
00:15:51,883 --> 00:15:55,812
He is dressed like a pilot!
It is really rare!

156
00:15:56,939 --> 00:16:00,868
But I did not cry...
Not in front of them.

157
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,703
Look who's coming!

158
00:16:25,324 --> 00:16:28,936
Look who's come back!
The little fairy with the stamps!

159
00:16:42,318 --> 00:16:45,929
You know, you're pretty cute
up close...

160
00:16:46,222 --> 00:16:48,491
Even if you wear glasses!

161
00:16:49,837 --> 00:16:53,002
So very cute...
Too bad you're a fairy!

162
00:16:58,765 --> 00:17:02,181
- Vitalic!
- Vitalic, we are here!

163
00:17:04,078 --> 00:17:05,933
We give up!
We give up!

164
00:17:06,894 --> 00:17:09,763
My friend Vitalic,
would like his stamps back,

165
00:17:10,190 --> 00:17:13,867
Especially the one with the Red Lenin.
- Stalin! With the Stalin!

166
00:17:16,878 --> 00:17:19,497
That's enough! Gagarin, that's enough!
We won!

167
00:17:28,303 --> 00:17:32,100
Now listen carefully, you momma's boy
'cause I'm only going to say this once.

168
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:36,328
Nobody in this city
touchs us, Siberians.

169
00:17:44,719 --> 00:17:50,032
Mama Siberia,
take my life!

170
00:17:50,032 --> 00:17:51,526
Shut up!

171
00:18:36,434 --> 00:18:40,012
First I'm going to release
the female.

172
00:18:45,363 --> 00:18:46,607
Wait...

173
00:18:47,634 --> 00:18:48,911
Now!

174
00:18:59,218 --> 00:19:00,625
You see, Kolyma...

175
00:19:01,107 --> 00:19:04,402
if they live only in a cage,
they die.

176
00:19:05,395 --> 00:19:10,959
Because the home of every living
creature is the sky.

177
00:19:39,348 --> 00:19:40,625
Go! Go!

178
00:19:43,637 --> 00:19:45,294
Stop there!

179
00:19:53,940 --> 00:19:55,729
Go!

180
00:19:56,564 --> 00:19:58,321
No! No!

181
00:19:59,029 --> 00:20:00,175
No!

182
00:20:00,661 --> 00:20:02,516
Go! Go!

183
00:20:03,189 --> 00:20:04,912
Go!

184
00:20:05,397 --> 00:20:06,959
Go! Run!

185
00:20:08,085 --> 00:20:10,835
Run! Run!

186
00:20:28,822 --> 00:20:30,677
- It's from Vaisef.
- Here!

187
00:20:34,007 --> 00:20:35,795
- It's from Sergei!
- He's my son.

188
00:20:40,983 --> 00:20:44,659
Mel, this is it!
It's from Gagarin.

189
00:20:47,287 --> 00:20:49,492
"They're keeping me seven years,
Kolyma.

190
00:20:50,456 --> 00:20:52,757
"They will be sending me
far away soon.

191
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:56,302
"But I'm OK.
I am tough.

192
00:20:56,824 --> 00:20:59,442
"These bastards
will never break me!

193
00:21:09,721 --> 00:21:12,175
The winter seemed never ending,

194
00:21:13,305 --> 00:21:16,436
and the pack was
dying of hunger.

195
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:21,874
The leader of the pack,
the oldest of all,

196
00:21:21,945 --> 00:21:26,517
was out in front, comforting
the young wolves

197
00:21:26,553 --> 00:21:29,782
telling them that
spring was coming.

198
00:21:31,641 --> 00:21:35,318
But, at a certain point,

199
00:21:36,249 --> 00:21:39,795
one young wolf
decides to stop.

200
00:21:40,313 --> 00:21:44,437
He says he has had enough
of cold and hunger,

201
00:21:45,178 --> 00:21:49,553
and he says he was
going to live among men.

202
00:21:50,266 --> 00:21:54,707
Because the important thing
is to stay alive.

203
00:21:55,226 --> 00:21:58,871
The young wolf
lets himself be caught,

204
00:21:59,803 --> 00:22:02,192
and with the passing
of time,

205
00:22:02,523 --> 00:22:05,273
He forgets he was ever a wolf.

206
00:22:07,867 --> 00:22:10,518
One day
many years later,

207
00:22:10,586 --> 00:22:13,336
as he was out hunting
with his master,

208
00:22:18,844 --> 00:22:21,910
He runs sevile
to collect the prey,

209
00:22:24,604 --> 00:22:30,070
but he realizes the prey
was the old leader of the pack.

210
00:22:34,364 --> 00:22:38,805
He falls silent with shame
but the old wolf speaks

211
00:22:39,196 --> 00:22:40,920
and says to him:

212
00:22:42,076 --> 00:22:46,492
"I die happy because
I lived my life as a wolf.

213
00:22:46,492 --> 00:22:51,194
"You, on the other hand, belong
neither to the world of wolves

214
00:22:51,228 --> 00:22:53,814
"Nor to the world of men!"

215
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:58,552
Hunger comes and goes,

216
00:22:58,589 --> 00:23:01,972
but dignity, once lost

217
00:23:04,861 --> 00:23:07,163
never returns.

218
00:23:21,502 --> 00:23:24,120
1989-1995
RIVERBANK, EX-SOVIET UNION

219
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:04,381
Kolyma, that girl
is looking at you.

220
00:24:05,439 --> 00:24:06,749
Really?

221
00:24:08,928 --> 00:24:11,546
Yeah, really.

222
00:24:14,688 --> 00:24:16,597
- Do you know her?
- No.

223
00:24:17,343 --> 00:24:19,962
- Do you?
- Never seen her before.

224
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,041
But I'd sure remember if I had.

225
00:24:22,081 --> 00:24:23,259
Kolyma, we gotta go!

226
00:24:52,098 --> 00:24:54,815
You sure took your time coming back!

227
00:25:03,362 --> 00:25:05,729
Mel, don't tell me
you don't recognize him.

228
00:25:06,498 --> 00:25:09,760
- Gagarin!
- Gagarin?

229
00:25:10,723 --> 00:25:11,970
Shit!

230
00:25:11,970 --> 00:25:14,839
Gagarin has gone back
to Riverbank!

231
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:29,822
My mother
I only wrote once

232
00:25:30,244 --> 00:25:32,382
and that was to tell me
she had sold the house

233
00:25:32,420 --> 00:25:34,459
and run off with some
truck driver from Romania.

234
00:25:35,235 --> 00:25:37,145
They say that Romanians
make good lovers!

235
00:25:41,636 --> 00:25:43,261
What's that?

236
00:25:44,963 --> 00:25:46,906
Just a little something from
my friends inside

237
00:25:47,204 --> 00:25:49,113
to make sure
I won't forget them.

238
00:25:50,628 --> 00:25:53,148
So, what are you doing here in the station?

239
00:25:53,316 --> 00:25:54,974
Copper, good stuff.

240
00:25:56,580 --> 00:25:58,402
- And who's paying?
- The gimp.

241
00:25:59,012 --> 00:26:00,354
As always.

242
00:26:02,053 --> 00:26:04,508
Hey listen, you should be happy
with the price I gave you.

243
00:26:04,901 --> 00:26:06,395
That is my final offer.

244
00:26:06,596 --> 00:26:08,931
You think you're dealing with
a bunch of idiots, don't you, gimp?

245
00:26:09,124 --> 00:26:11,906
Well you're wrong.
We're only asking for what's fair.

246
00:26:13,764 --> 00:26:16,416
- And what would "fair" be?
- Three times as much.

247
00:26:16,996 --> 00:26:18,426
Three times?

248
00:26:19,110 --> 00:26:21,346
You Siberians
are out of your mind!

249
00:26:25,381 --> 00:26:28,065
- Mel, where does he keep the money?
- In the office.

250
00:26:28,326 --> 00:26:29,918
- Gagarin, don't...
- Hurry up!

251
00:26:36,039 --> 00:26:38,527
- Jesus Christ, got it!
- Alright.

252
00:26:40,134 --> 00:26:43,134
- Come on, let's get outta this fucking dump
- No, Gagarin.

253
00:26:45,991 --> 00:26:47,485
We said what's fair.

254
00:26:50,471 --> 00:26:51,813
Fair?

255
00:26:53,222 --> 00:26:55,710
And what, exactly,
is fair, Kolyma?

256
00:26:58,055 --> 00:27:00,772
There is no such thing as "fair".

257
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:05,759
- So how did it happen?
- Mama!

258
00:27:07,815 --> 00:27:09,244
Mom!

259
00:27:13,639 --> 00:27:16,508
Nobody has been here since
husband was killed.

260
00:27:18,503 --> 00:27:21,154
Here kept all his fishing
gear in here.

261
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:37,830
Are you sure, you don't
have a better place to live?

262
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,457
There is no better
than seeing

263
00:27:40,457 --> 00:27:42,628
you and Vitalic
every morning, Aunt Katya.

264
00:27:48,968 --> 00:27:50,278
Move!

265
00:28:17,705 --> 00:28:19,495
We're not going to arrest you.

266
00:28:20,075 --> 00:28:22,376
If you do not tell me where Ageyev
and his men are,

267
00:28:23,146 --> 00:28:26,114
I'll kill you. Simple as that.

268
00:28:26,571 --> 00:28:28,578
Our jails are full
of people like you.

269
00:28:29,226 --> 00:28:32,706
So try and act
intelligently.

270
00:28:36,139 --> 00:28:38,725
Ageyev is very powerful.

271
00:28:39,403 --> 00:28:41,159
He's got a lot of men.

272
00:28:41,292 --> 00:28:43,680
And this is his territory.

273
00:28:43,819 --> 00:28:45,762
When he finds out you have taken us,

274
00:28:46,092 --> 00:28:49,223
He will kill us all!

275
00:28:51,115 --> 00:28:53,254
It would be better to die...

276
00:29:11,468 --> 00:29:12,897
Shit, I can't believe it!

277
00:29:13,133 --> 00:29:16,516
After 7 years, I find myself
right back where I started from.

278
00:29:18,316 --> 00:29:20,291
- What's with them?
- Russian army.

279
00:29:20,589 --> 00:29:22,629
When the Soviet Union fell,
they left.

280
00:29:22,861 --> 00:29:25,032
Then they changed their flags
and came back.

281
00:29:25,229 --> 00:29:26,822
Now they're even worse
before.

282
00:29:26,862 --> 00:29:29,612
Supposedly they're here to help
the peace process.

283
00:29:29,612 --> 00:29:31,850
Ya, to protect us.

284
00:29:32,525 --> 00:29:35,111
But all they really care about
are the weapons factories.

285
00:29:35,725 --> 00:29:38,059
A lot of the clans are
making deals with them.

286
00:29:43,373 --> 00:29:44,551
And those?

287
00:29:44,590 --> 00:29:46,859
They shot up overnight,
like mushrooms.

288
00:29:47,342 --> 00:29:51,020
So now the poor are dying of envy
as well as hunger.

289
00:29:51,214 --> 00:29:52,687
That's their fucking problem.

290
00:29:52,687 --> 00:29:55,342
I'm sure as hell not going to stick
around to enjoy the view.

291
00:29:55,342 --> 00:29:58,342
- What are you going to do?
- To get rich.

292
00:29:58,703 --> 00:30:02,085
That's a good one! Nobody in
Riverbank has ever gotten rich.

293
00:30:02,958 --> 00:30:05,325
Well, I guess that means that
I'll be the first.

294
00:30:07,823 --> 00:30:09,383
Bring me to see the city!

295
00:30:14,575 --> 00:30:16,845
This is 'bank.
Can you really recognize it!

296
00:30:17,647 --> 00:30:21,193
Completely in the hands of
Georgians now: weapons, black market...

297
00:30:21,871 --> 00:30:23,878
They call this Odessa now.

298
00:30:24,048 --> 00:30:25,456
The Jews control it.

299
00:30:25,456 --> 00:30:28,303
Diamonds, precious stones...

300
00:30:30,383 --> 00:30:33,613
This is Bridges:
prostitution, drugs...

301
00:30:34,543 --> 00:30:36,486
even a few Black Seed bastards.

302
00:30:37,616 --> 00:30:39,526
Why are they bastards?

303
00:30:40,272 --> 00:30:42,126
What the fuck do you know about
the Black Seed?

304
00:30:42,192 --> 00:30:44,494
Shit, Gagarin, just look at them.
They look like clowns!

305
00:30:44,529 --> 00:30:46,383
All covered in gold and no
respect for women...

306
00:30:46,767 --> 00:30:50,150
You do not know...
You're the one who doesn't know shit,Kolyma!

307
00:30:52,689 --> 00:30:56,202
When I was in jail, if it were not
the Black Seed, I'd be dead.

308
00:31:01,745 --> 00:31:03,982
Come on, brother, take me around!

309
00:31:07,569 --> 00:31:09,512
Bring me to see the world. Come on!

310
00:31:49,427 --> 00:31:50,801
Go! Go!

311
00:32:13,939 --> 00:32:15,369
What time is it?

312
00:32:17,397 --> 00:32:18,738
Almost five.

313
00:32:19,188 --> 00:32:21,195
Your friend with the truck
isn't showing up.

314
00:32:22,100 --> 00:32:24,686
- We're going to have to walk back
- But it's far!

315
00:32:24,756 --> 00:32:27,277
And dangerous, too!
We're in Bridges.

316
00:32:29,269 --> 00:32:32,236
Here! Put this on.

317
00:32:32,917 --> 00:32:34,990
Come on, let's get a move on.

318
00:33:11,254 --> 00:33:13,491
I was just asking myself...

319
00:33:13,527 --> 00:33:17,301
what a bunch of Siberians
are doing in Bridges!

320
00:33:19,703 --> 00:33:23,381
- Ghat, did you invite them?
- Not me!

321
00:33:23,415 --> 00:33:26,284
So why the hell are they here?

322
00:33:26,454 --> 00:33:28,822
There is enough shit around here already.

323
00:33:29,687 --> 00:33:32,469
Can one of you Siberians tell me,
Why you are here?

324
00:33:32,663 --> 00:33:35,565
Did you ask permission to
come on to our turf?

325
00:33:35,863 --> 00:33:37,205
And armed!

326
00:33:40,024 --> 00:33:41,551
We're on our way home.

327
00:33:43,352 --> 00:33:46,930
I am Gagarin, from Riverbank. Let us pass.

328
00:33:47,319 --> 00:33:48,881
Advice for a friend.

329
00:33:49,688 --> 00:33:52,623
And I am Vulture,
from Bridges.

330
00:33:53,113 --> 00:33:57,488
And Vulture does not take advice
from anybody!

331
00:34:00,825 --> 00:34:03,639
Well, then Vulture is an asshole.

332
00:34:07,224 --> 00:34:08,948
Get them!

333
00:35:02,491 --> 00:35:03,865
Welcome.

334
00:35:04,027 --> 00:35:07,856
I'm doctor Nikolai Sakurov,
and this is my daughter, Xenya.

335
00:35:08,700 --> 00:35:10,740
It's best you don't move.

336
00:35:10,972 --> 00:35:12,532
You can stay with us tonight.

337
00:35:12,988 --> 00:35:15,192
We wouldn't want to trouble you, Doctor.

338
00:35:15,383 --> 00:35:16,952
Trouble?

339
00:35:17,723 --> 00:35:21,660
My dear woman, my daughter and I
have been welcomed like family

340
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:23,765
Ever since we came
to Riverbank.

341
00:35:24,219 --> 00:35:28,759
I feel like a member of this community,
not the director of the regional hospital.

342
00:35:31,517 --> 00:35:35,794
Okay, confirmed. They're the
drug traffickers we were looking for.

343
00:35:36,157 --> 00:35:38,460
We'll attack as soon as
our guest tells us

344
00:35:38,460 --> 00:35:40,185
where Ageyev's hideout is.

345
00:35:41,085 --> 00:35:43,769
By the way, Headquarters tells me

346
00:35:43,965 --> 00:35:47,064
that someone with Ageyev
we have to watch out for...

347
00:35:47,229 --> 00:35:52,150
considered highly dangerous.
A certain Yuri Lebedev.

348
00:35:52,893 --> 00:35:54,649
A Siberian, like you.

349
00:35:56,477 --> 00:35:58,452
Goes by the name of Gagarin.

350
00:36:00,638 --> 00:36:02,165
Never heard of him.

351
00:36:02,814 --> 00:36:04,797
I guess we'll meet him soon enough.

352
00:36:04,797 --> 00:36:06,936
You work on him,
I'll leave you alone.

353
00:36:32,799 --> 00:36:34,654
I made you some tea and

354
00:36:34,687 --> 00:36:36,476
Papa said you could
eat some cookies.

355
00:36:56,864 --> 00:36:59,036
Was this the knife
that hurt you?

356
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:03,382
- No, this is a tattoo.
- This hurt you, right?

357
00:37:06,785 --> 00:37:11,673
- You like this book?
- Yes, it's beautiful.

358
00:37:11,713 --> 00:37:14,688
- Do you want it?
- But it's not yours, it's your father's.

359
00:37:14,688 --> 00:37:17,471
Everything here is mine,
the house, yard...

360
00:37:18,337 --> 00:37:19,766
My father is mine.

361
00:37:20,128 --> 00:37:23,478
- Do you want the yard?
- No, the book is plenty.

362
00:37:23,745 --> 00:37:24,989
Good.

363
00:37:31,777 --> 00:37:34,298
Papa says that I'm special,

364
00:37:34,337 --> 00:37:36,409
and that I play the piano well.

365
00:37:36,705 --> 00:37:38,974
- And you?
- I'm no-not the piano...

366
00:37:39,041 --> 00:37:41,376
Not the piano.
Special!

367
00:37:43,138 --> 00:37:44,665
And you're special, too?

368
00:37:47,490 --> 00:37:50,807
Once, when once I was four,
I won the record for beatings.

369
00:37:50,978 --> 00:37:53,913
My father beat me for half an hour
and I didn't cry.

370
00:37:54,114 --> 00:37:55,391
Not once.

371
00:37:55,682 --> 00:37:57,690
- Why?
- Why what?

372
00:37:57,923 --> 00:38:00,923
- Why did not you cry?
- Because men don't cry.

373
00:38:05,187 --> 00:38:08,765
Oh! Poor men!
It is good to cry!

374
00:38:09,091 --> 00:38:11,479
Are you happy when you cry?

375
00:38:12,578 --> 00:38:14,619
That is too hard a question.

376
00:38:16,964 --> 00:38:18,873
This is what I think.
I think...

377
00:38:20,644 --> 00:38:25,248
that you do not cry,
but I do not read.

378
00:38:25,604 --> 00:38:27,262
And that is worse than crying!

379
00:38:27,460 --> 00:38:29,248
What do you mean you don't read?

380
00:38:30,308 --> 00:38:34,498
Xenya does not know how to read.
Poor Xenya!

381
00:38:37,156 --> 00:38:39,774
You can find someone
to read to you.

382
00:38:40,196 --> 00:38:42,879
- Will you read to me?
- Of course!

383
00:38:47,396 --> 00:38:48,705
Here!

384
00:38:49,988 --> 00:38:52,923
"With yards of sunset yard

385
00:38:52,965 --> 00:38:55,780
"Along the Nevsky of the world,

386
00:38:55,780 --> 00:38:58,082
"With its glowing trail

387
00:38:58,405 --> 00:39:02,083
"I linger with a Don Giovanni air. "

388
00:39:03,654 --> 00:39:05,988
It's by a poet named Mayakovsky.

389
00:39:06,501 --> 00:39:09,762
But do not ask me what it means,
I did not understand a word.

390
00:39:10,245 --> 00:39:13,594
Xenya does not read
and Kolyma does not understand.

391
00:39:34,310 --> 00:39:36,285
Kolyma!

392
00:39:38,727 --> 00:39:40,996
- What is that?
- Kolyma!

393
00:39:41,158 --> 00:39:44,060
The new doctor's daughter. She
arrived the same day you came back.

394
00:39:46,183 --> 00:39:51,485
- She's got it all going!
- Except she's not all there in the head.

395
00:40:26,793 --> 00:40:28,767
She's fine, thank you!

396
00:40:29,449 --> 00:40:31,871
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm okay.

397
00:40:32,841 --> 00:40:35,262
I guess Xenya's glad to
have found Kolyma.

398
00:40:38,121 --> 00:40:41,569
That's very nice, Xenya but
you should really go home now.

399
00:40:42,153 --> 00:40:45,830
People of Riverbank,
I, Yuri Lebedev

400
00:40:45,897 --> 00:40:47,370
also known as Gagarin,

401
00:40:47,370 --> 00:40:50,086
inform you that I have had
enough of this shit

402
00:40:50,506 --> 00:40:53,223
Therefore, I have decided to kill myself.

403
00:40:53,514 --> 00:40:55,423
Farewell, you shitfaces!

404
00:41:12,235 --> 00:41:14,406
Do not worry, Xenya
he'll come up now.

405
00:41:14,763 --> 00:41:16,137
He's probably swimming
under the boat.

406
00:41:17,035 --> 00:41:19,174
No, he's not coming back up.

407
00:41:19,659 --> 00:41:23,074
Gagarin, stop being such a jerk!
Come up now, asshole!

408
00:41:23,115 --> 00:41:26,083
- He's not coming up.
- Mel, stop horsing around!

409
00:41:26,284 --> 00:41:29,665
He's not even there, Kolyma.
Maybe he drowned.

410
00:41:29,931 --> 00:41:31,371
Do not believe it, Xenya.

411
00:41:31,371 --> 00:41:34,187
Gagarin, he always makes
jokes like that.

412
00:41:34,187 --> 00:41:35,845
He's just making jokes.

413
00:41:45,099 --> 00:41:48,296
See? I can stay under
for two whole minutes.

414
00:41:52,300 --> 00:41:54,886
- What's wrong with her?
- She's crying, for you.

415
00:41:55,884 --> 00:41:59,015
See, what did I tell you?
It was all a joke.

416
00:41:59,373 --> 00:42:01,413
Nothing can kill Gagarin.

417
00:42:06,444 --> 00:42:08,932
Don't worry, Xenya, it'll be alright.
You'll be okay.

418
00:42:14,573 --> 00:42:16,482
Are you really crying for me?

419
00:42:18,157 --> 00:42:21,605
Let me tell you, it is not worth it.

420
00:42:22,862 --> 00:42:25,545
Nobody has ever cried for me.

421
00:42:40,622 --> 00:42:45,095
People call them crazy,
insane, abnormal...

422
00:42:45,390 --> 00:42:49,449
all because we don't understand
what they're thinking and saying.

423
00:42:50,223 --> 00:42:53,191
But their language is the language of God.

424
00:42:54,159 --> 00:42:57,421
That is why they are called
"A Gift from God."

425
00:42:59,727 --> 00:43:02,223
And we must
respect them all.

426
00:43:02,223 --> 00:43:06,217
Nobody is allowed
to lay a finger on them,

427
00:43:06,255 --> 00:43:08,394
and it's up to us
to protect them

428
00:43:08,591 --> 00:43:11,690
even if it cost us our lives.

429
00:43:12,943 --> 00:43:18,410
Now, let's drink our "Chifir,"
The best tea in the whole world.

430
00:43:19,152 --> 00:43:22,283
First we enjoy its warmth

431
00:43:23,344 --> 00:43:27,654
and we appreciate its aroma,

432
00:43:28,816 --> 00:43:33,552
and only then do we taste its flavour.

433
00:43:41,809 --> 00:43:44,843
Three pleasures in one.

434
00:43:44,946 --> 00:43:48,077
And think it is only just water!

435
00:43:53,330 --> 00:43:55,632
Kolyma draws.

436
00:43:57,362 --> 00:44:00,209
He wants to study with you.

437
00:44:00,946 --> 00:44:03,401
I cannot say if he is any good

438
00:44:04,305 --> 00:44:07,601
but maybe you could kindly
look and see

439
00:44:07,634 --> 00:44:10,983
if our Holy Mother
guides his hand.

440
00:44:16,306 --> 00:44:21,489
There is nothing for me to read.
Like an empty notebook.

441
00:44:21,939 --> 00:44:25,255
Clean, white pages
waiting to be filled.

442
00:44:27,379 --> 00:44:29,582
Kolyma, this is Ink

443
00:44:29,811 --> 00:44:31,634
master of tattoos.

444
00:44:38,547 --> 00:44:42,541
Yes, the Mother by
the grace of our Lord,

445
00:44:43,156 --> 00:44:45,195
has blessed your hands.

446
00:44:45,716 --> 00:44:47,373
But...

447
00:44:47,539 --> 00:44:51,883
a tattoo is not simply a drawing.

448
00:44:52,532 --> 00:44:55,848
A tattoo artist
is like a confessor.

449
00:44:55,892 --> 00:44:59,635
He writes the story of a man
on his body.

450
00:45:06,805 --> 00:45:11,061
Mans' lives can all
seem all the same.

451
00:45:11,412 --> 00:45:14,707
You're born, you grow up,
you fall in love,

452
00:45:14,773 --> 00:45:17,162
You have children, you work

453
00:45:18,357 --> 00:45:20,016
You die.

454
00:45:21,076 --> 00:45:25,550
Some enjoy life,
Some don't.

455
00:45:25,941 --> 00:45:30,829
But we Siberians, Kolyma,
we fight it.

456
00:45:33,014 --> 00:45:35,250
You must do your very best to learn.

457
00:45:36,117 --> 00:45:38,932
For many months
you will do only one thing.

458
00:45:40,630 --> 00:45:42,288
Observe.

459
00:45:44,502 --> 00:45:46,641
I heard one of his men
is a real cop hunter.

460
00:45:47,349 --> 00:45:50,514
Something fierce, a different
breed from the rest of you.

461
00:45:51,863 --> 00:45:53,520
Comes somewhere far away.

462
00:45:53,686 --> 00:45:56,851
I do not know, believe me.
I'm not that important.

463
00:45:57,175 --> 00:46:00,524
Ageyev has got a lot of
good strong men.

464
00:46:00,950 --> 00:46:02,707
You will never catch him.

465
00:46:03,574 --> 00:46:05,942
Because Allah
is on his side.

466
00:46:07,383 --> 00:46:10,613
That's funny, cause I'm pretty sure
he is on my side.

467
00:46:11,671 --> 00:46:13,329
God helps one side sometimes

468
00:46:13,751 --> 00:46:15,442
and sometimes he
helps the other.

469
00:46:16,663 --> 00:46:19,314
What matters is being on
the right side at the right moment.

470
00:46:26,648 --> 00:46:29,496
No, no, please!
I dunno a thing!

471
00:46:29,496 --> 00:46:31,438
I know nothing!
No, please!

472
00:46:41,177 --> 00:46:42,421
Get out of here!

473
00:46:43,193 --> 00:46:46,608
You don't know shit, and another death
isn't going to do anybody any good.

474
00:46:47,865 --> 00:46:49,937
And maybe because God
is on your side right now.

475
00:46:52,505 --> 00:46:54,414
So go before he changes his mind.

476
00:46:56,281 --> 00:46:58,168
How you say "crazy"
where you come from?

477
00:47:03,097 --> 00:47:05,039
We say, "Gift from God."

478
00:47:16,346 --> 00:47:19,098
Kolyma, get up!
The river is flooding.

479
00:47:19,098 --> 00:47:21,912
It's already washed away
some houses from the banks.

480
00:47:22,171 --> 00:47:24,310
Come on, they need all the help
they can get.

481
00:47:52,987 --> 00:47:55,377
- Vitalic!
- Kolyma!

482
00:47:56,380 --> 00:47:58,747
The river is washing away everything!

483
00:47:58,747 --> 00:48:00,985
Gagarin and Mel are
already down at the canal.

484
00:48:01,051 --> 00:48:03,059
There is all kinds of stuff you can have!

485
00:48:03,101 --> 00:48:05,883
Grandfather Kuzya says we have to
help the others down at the river.

486
00:48:06,076 --> 00:48:07,320
Shit, Kolyma!

487
00:48:07,388 --> 00:48:09,778
There are so many helping already.

488
00:48:09,820 --> 00:48:11,260
For once, we don't have to steal

489
00:48:11,260 --> 00:48:12,569
or take out our knives!

490
00:48:12,604 --> 00:48:13,978
Please!

491
00:48:19,645 --> 00:48:23,922
- Kolyma!
- Get back inside Xenya! It's pouring here.

492
00:48:23,964 --> 00:48:26,652
Papa is at the hospital.
Xenya is all alone!

493
00:48:26,652 --> 00:48:28,147
Wait for me, I'm coming with you!

494
00:48:28,220 --> 00:48:30,359
It is dangerous, the river
isn't normal today!

495
00:48:30,429 --> 00:48:34,739
I know it is not normal! But Xenya
is not normal, neither are you!

496
00:48:34,813 --> 00:48:37,758
Damnit, Xenya, I told you that
you're not coming with us!

497
00:48:37,758 --> 00:48:38,902
But why?

498
00:48:38,941 --> 00:48:43,481
I'm not a little girl, you know.
I'm not a little girl!

499
00:48:44,414 --> 00:48:46,137
I am not going to be killed out there.

500
00:48:46,205 --> 00:48:49,149
If I wanted to die,
I would do it myself!

501
00:48:49,149 --> 00:48:51,059
Stop it! Go inside!

502
00:48:55,039 --> 00:48:56,894
